Vice President Mike Pence gave a speech at Fort Bragg, North Carolina, expressing gratitude and appreciation to the men and women who serve in the United States Army and the Joint Special Operations Command. He praised them as the greatest soldiers on Earth and highlighted their important role in protecting the nation's freedom. Pence also mentioned the support and sacrifices made by military families. He emphasized that President Donald Trump is committed to rebuilding the military and providing the necessary resources for its success. Pence acknowledged the challenges and threats faced by the armed forces and urged them to remain vigilant, respect the chain of command, and take care of one another. He concluded by assuring the soldiers that they have the support and prayers of the American people.